<db:para>If you are going to build QDoc from source, the following prerequisites apply:</db:para>
<db:orderedlist numeration="arabic">
<db:listitem>
<db:para>Install <db:link xlink:href="http://clang.llvm.org">LLVM 6.0</db:link> or greater. The pre-built binaries needed can be found <db:link xlink:href="http://releases.llvm.org/download.html">here</db:link>.</db:para>
</db:listitem>
<db:listitem>
<db:para>Set the environment variable <db:code>LLVM_INSTALL_DIR</db:code> to point to the directory where LLVM is installed. This should be the top level directory. For example, on a Linux or macOS system with LLVM installed to <db:code>/usr/llvm</db:code>:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp" role="bad">$ export LLVM_INSTALL_DIR=/usr/llvm
</db:programlisting>
<db:para>On a Windows system with LLVM installed to <db:code>C:\Program Files\LLVM</db:code>:</db:para>
<db:programlisting language="cpp" role="bad">C:\&amp;gt; setx LLVM_INSTALL_DIR &quot;C:\Program Files\LLVM&quot;
</db:programlisting>
</db:listitem>
</db:orderedlist>
